    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractLauncher

        public AbstractLauncher(Class applicationClass,
                        Class<L> launchableClass)
                 throws InstantiationException
        Constructor prepares the launcher and registers already a shutdown hook. The launcher class is used to instantiate a new launcher instance if the instantiateLaunchable() method is not overwritten. After instantiation of this class the launcher must be initialized and activated before the RSB interface is provided.
        Parameters:
        launchableClass - the class to be launched.
        applicationClass - the class representing this application. Those is used for scope generation if the getName() method is not overwritten.
        Throws:
        InstantiationException

        Description copied from class: RSBCommunicationService

These behavior guarantees a proper component shutdown without skipping any parts because of exception handling.
